{
  "text": "The amygdala-lesioned animals, as compared to control and hippocampus-lesioned animals, also retrieved a food reward placed near emotionally salient objects both more quickly and most frequently. This finding provided another indication that they were behaviorally uninhibited in the presence of salient objects. These findings are consistent with testing performed with adult animals with amygdala lesions (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
